formula: T(n, k) = Sum_{d|n} mu(n/d) * A081720(n,k) for k<=n.
mathematica: t[n_, k_] := Sum[EulerPhi[d] k^(n/d), {d, Divisors[n]}]/(2n) + (k^Floor[(n+1)/2] + k^Ceiling[(n+1)/2])/4;
T[n_, k_] := Sum[MoebiusMu[d] t[n/d, k], {d, Divisors[n]}];
Table[T[n-k+1, k], {n, 1, 11}, {k, n, 1, -1}] // Flatten (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Mar 26 2020 *)
